attributeList.attribute: Required for pheromone-induced cell cycle arrest and for caspase-10-induced death. Caspase-10 induces the dephosphorylation of the autophagy inducer protein, ATG13, and of RAD53. FAR11 interacts with PP2A (CPX-1856/CPX-1857/CPX-1858/CPX-1859) therefore the FAR complex may target PP2A to regulate ATG13 and RAD53 phosphorylation, and thus induce autophagy and DNA damage-induced arrest.
